                            <comment id="13427480" author="karasiuk" created="Thu, 2 Aug 2012 18:45:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;In looking through the class code for org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser there is a reference to org.apache.commons.logging.LogFactory in a static initializer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;static {};&lt;br/&gt;
      0  ldc_w &amp;lt;Class org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;153&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      3  invokestatic org.apache.commons.logging.LogFactory.getLog(java.lang.Class) : org.apache.commons.logging.Log &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;154&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      6  putstatic org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.BaseParser.LOG : org.apache.commons.logging.Log &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;39&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I searched through all the nested files in the tika-bundle and could not find the org.apache.commons.logging.LogFactory class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427997" author="karasiuk" created="Fri, 3 Aug 2012 12:18:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I can confirm, that when I patched the tika-bundle (by adding the commons-logging-1.1.1.jar to it), that this problem went away.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I currently have a working OSGi Tika application on Linux. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately the PDF parsing hangs on Macosx. The PDF parser causes a number of system libraries to be loaded, and for some reason it hangs while trying to load the AWT library.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13428887" author="jukkaz" created="Sun, 5 Aug 2012 18:57:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The lack of the Commons Logging dependency is actually intentional, though the fact that is&apos;s marked as optional in the bundle manifest is not. I fixed that in revision 1369624.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason why we&apos;d rather not include the logging library inside tika-bundle is that a deployment probably wants to use something like Pax Logging or another OSGi Log service implementation to control how log messages are handled. That&apos;s only possible if tika-bundle imports the logging packages from another bundle.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
